no this is not an exageration. <p>"talking to you is the conversational equivalent of an out of body experience"<br>Suzie, Calvin & Hobbes</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umahtstohlit.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Maht Stohlit</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/16/01 9:37:52 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.murray-ky.net/~maht/EverQuest/cards.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ok I am convinced</span><hr size=1> My advice if you're starting on Rallos is go to Tox.  = )  Tox/Warrens etc. is about the only place I've found on the server that you won't find very many twink PKs.  They tend to hang out in the more populated areas like Gfay/EC/Qeynos Hills.  There's nothing more annoying than being about to kill someone and their 50+ druid friend healing and buffing them. =P  PKs usually come in packs, so make friends early, but don't trust anyone you haven't been around for a while.  Some people only group with you so they can find out what level you are so they know if they have a shot at PK'ing you. = )<br>
<br>
Whenever someone inspects, move.  When someone inspects they're looking for 2 things.  1) To see if you have anything they want.  2) To see if you have gear that they wouldn't be able to beat.  If you move, they may THINK you've got something they want...but they're also not going to KNOW you can't beat them.<br>
<br>
If you think you're going to be low on life after a fight, give up the fight.  It stinks finishing off a mob and feeling excited about it only to zone out and have the people who trained you waiting there to PK you ;-)<br>
<br>
Take everything with a grain of salt.  Don't expect to be able to level up to a point where no one can beat you because there's always someone somewhere higher, better, or with more friends than you.  When someone taunts you they're trying to get a rise out of you...if you don't let it bother you, they get a bit less satisfaction.<br>
<br>
Don't make threats you can't back up.  (ie, don't make threats).  Someone PKs you, let it go.  Add them to your list of 'People to jump later in life.'  Get a couple friends and go back for him and his friends.  Catch him alone in a dark alley, etc.  Don't tell him you're going to bring hordes of friends, don't tell him you're going to pay him back...just do it. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umahtstohlit.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Maht Stohlit</A> at: 9/16/01 9:38:22 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukambic.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kambic</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/16/01 9:38:50 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://kambic.homestead.com/files/ribbon_small.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ok I am convinced</span><hr size=1> Dont... play... on... Rallos... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubalaffdishwasher.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Balaff Dishwasher</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/22/01 10:34:28 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ok I am convinced</span><hr size=1> Play TZ, VZ seems to be in poor shape last I checked. SZ is cool too, but I got bored there quick. Red Servers &gt; Blue Servers. <p>I will wash your dishes</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ucoyoteblack.showPublicProfile?language=EN>coyoteblack</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/24